This program allows the user to draw three different types of shapes in the console:
a snowman, stairs, and a rectangle. The program first asks the user for three size inputs
to create the snowman, which consists of a head, body, and base. The head includes eyes, and
each section is drawn with stars forming a border. Next, the program asks for a size to draw
stairs, printing steps that grow in length row by row. Finally, the program asks for a size 
to draw a square-shaped rectangle. The code is organized into classes (Snowman, Stairs, and 
Rectangle) with methods to handle the drawing, and a main entry point that runs all three drawing 
functions sequentially. This structure makes the code modular, easy to read, and allows each shape 
to be drawn independently.